        body: "Non-compete enforceability varies dramatically by state. California, North Dakota, Oklahoma, and Minnesota essentially prohibit employment non-competes. Many other states enforce them only if they meet strict tests of reasonableness: the restriction must be no broader than necessary to protect a legitimate business interest, must not impose an undue hardship on the employee, and must not harm the public interest.\n\nIn 2024, the FTC proposed a near-total ban on employment non-competes, though legal challenges have complicated implementation. The trend nationally is toward narrowing non-compete enforcement, especially for lower-wage workers. Before requiring employees to sign non-competes, consult a licensed employment attorney in the state where your employees work.",
